{"title_page": "2020 Indiana gubernatorial election", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 gubernatorial election in Indiana, USA}}\n{{see also|2020 United States gubernatorial elections}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name      = 2020 Indiana gubernatorial election\n| country            = Indiana\n| type               = presidential\n| ongoing            = yes\n| previous_election  = 2016 Indiana gubernatorial election\n| previous_year      = 2016\n| next_election      = 2024 Indiana gubernatorial election\n| next_year          = 2024\n| election_date      = November 3, 2020\n| image1             = [[File:Holcomb Official Headshot (49639997842) (cropped).jpg|x150px]]\n| nominee1           = [[Eric Holcomb]]\n| party1             = Republican Party (United States)\n| popular_vote1      = \n| percentage1        = \n| image2             = [[File:No image.svg|x150px]]\n| nominee2           = [[Woody Myers]]\n| party2             = Democratic Party (United States)\n| popular_vote2      = \n| percentage2        =\n| title              = Governor\n| before_election    = [[Eric Holcomb]]\n| before_party       = Republican Party (United States)\n}}\n{{ElectionsIN}}\n\nThe '''2020 Indiana gubernatorial election''' will be held on November 3, 2020, to elect the [[Governor of Indiana]], concurrently with the [[2020 United States presidential election|2020 U.S. presidential election]], as well as [[2020 United States House of Representatives elections|elections]] to the [[United States House of Representatives]] and various [[2020 United States elections#State elections|state]] and [[2020 United States elections#Local elections|local elections]]. Incumbent [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] Governor [[Eric Holcomb]] is eligible to run for re-election to a second term in office, and announced his intention to do so on July 13, 2019.<ref name=\"Reelection\">{{cite news |last1=Smith |first1=Casey |title=Gov. Eric Holcomb to run for reelection: 'Let's keep making Hoosier history for four more years' |url=https://www.indystar.com/story/news/politics/elections/2019/07/13/gov-eric-holcomb-officially-announces-his-bid-re-election/1674492001/ |accessdate=13 July 2019 |work=[[Indianapolis Star]] |date=July 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Republican primary==\n===Candidates===\n====Declared====\n*[[Eric Holcomb]], incumbent Governor<ref name=\"Reelection\" />\n\n====Removed from ballot====\n*Brian Roth, businessman<ref>{{cite news |last1=Erdody |first1=Lindsey |title=Carmel Republican planning election run against Holcomb |url=https://www.ibj.com/articles/carmel-republican-plans-to-run-against-holcomb |accessdate=September 10, 2019 |work=Indianapolis Business Journal |date=September 10, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Smith |first1=Brandon |title=Carmel Republican Files For Potential Holcomb Challenge |url=https://www.wfyi.org/news/articles/carmel-republican-files-for-potential-holcomb-challenge |accessdate=September 21, 2019 |work=WFYI |date=September 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Sikich |first1=Chris |title=Westfield Republican signs up to challenge Gov. Holcomb in primary |url=https://www.indystar.com/story/news/politics/elections/2019/09/11/westfield-republican-to-challenge-gov-holcomb-in-primary/2286357001/ |accessdate=23 September 2019 |work=Indianapolis Star |date=September 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Berman |first1=Eric |title=CHALLENGERS TO HOLCOMB AND BAIRD BOOTED FROM PRIMARY BALLOT |url=https://www.wibc.com/news/local-indiana/challengers-to-holcomb-and-baird-booted-from-primary-ballot/ |accessdate=22 February 2020 |work=WIBC |date=February 21, 2020}}</ref>\n\n====Declined====\n*[[Curtis Hill]], [[Attorney General of Indiana]] (running for re-election)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://howeypolitics.com/Content/Default/Howey-s-Daily-Beacon/Article/Hill-challenging-Holcomb-A-fool-s-errand/-3/383/17391|title=Hill challenging Holcomb? A fool's errand|website=howeypolitics.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Indiana At